history.content:
I am having a hard time deciding what classes to take. I am a second year undeclared CS and Data Science Major (can declare both after this semester).

For spring, I want to take CS 170, Data 100, and CS 161 OR CS W186.

Then in the fall, I want to take CS 162, Stat 140, and Math 53.

I know CS 170 will be a high workload class so I do not want to pair it with another high workload upper div. Between CS 161 and CS W186, which class has the more manageable workload and is better suited to be paired with CS 170 and Data 100?

*edit: For reference I am currently enrolled in CS 61C and CS 70 and find the combination to be challenging.
history.subject: Workload for CS Upper Divs (CS 161 vs CS W186)
